<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
In OS_Console_CopyOut the variable return_code is assigned OS_ERROR immediately before entering a while(true) loop that always sets return_code (to OS_SUCCESS when the end of string is reached, or OS_QUEUE_FULL when the buffer is full) before any break/return. There is no path that uses the initial value of return_code, and the function always returns a value assigned inside the loop. Therefore the statement `return_code = OS_ERROR;` is executed but its removal would not affect program behaviour — it is redundant (dead) code.
</scenario>
